1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
vcf2report — turn a raw exome VCF into
an auditable ACMG report. Offline. In seconds.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:13,000
One command: point Claude at a VCF
and the patient's phenotype (HPO terms).

3
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:27,000
An app appears inside Claude:
a per-sample session and a command panel.

4
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Live phases — Local = the deterministic engine
on your machine · Claude = phenotype→HPO + narrative.

5
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:50,000
24,801 variants → 2 candidates,
fully offline (~3 seconds).

6
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:58,000
The result: a draft laudo (report).

7
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:08,000
SCN1A — Pathogenic (primary) ·
RB1 — Pathogenic (secondary, ACMG SF actionable).

8
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Not a black box: every ACMG criterion is shown.

9
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:31,000
PVS1 + PM2 + PP4 + PP5 → Pathogenic —
each with its source and date.

10
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:37,000
engine = decided deterministically ·
model = left for expert review.

11
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:45,000
Real databases, all local:
gnomAD v4.1 · full ClinVar · AlphaMissense.

12
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:52,000
The VCF never leaves the machine.

13
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Same engine, any phenotype:
Marfan, colorectal, renal, retinoblastoma…

14
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:12,000
AlphaMissense recovers a pathogenic missense:
PAX6 → Likely Pathogenic (0.9999) — VUS without it.

15
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Does it actually work? 200 real ClinVar variants —
ClinVar withheld from the engine (non-circular).

16
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:30,000
0 pathogenic-vs-benign flips ·
100% precision when it commits.

17
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:40,000
At scale: 5,335 real cases · 1,067 / 1,067
known ClinVar-pathogenic surfaced — 0 missed.

18
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:48,000
246 automated tests passing ·
everything reproducible offline.

19
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:54,000
Built with Claude Code —
hardened by multi-agent adversarial review.

20
00:02:54,500 --> 00:03:00,000
Draft aid, not a diagnostic device.
github.com/gbbarra/vcf2report
